==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lactide
<hw>Lac"tide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Lac</ets>tic +
anhydride.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white, crystalline
substance, obtained from lactic acid by distillation, and regarded as an
anhydride; also, by extension, any similar substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lactiferous</ent>⟦br⟧
